- The highest loss during testing refers to the maximum test loss value in the performance metrics for experiments categorized under the metric type 'loss'.;
- Details on configurations include batch size, validate loss improvement delta, patience, number of layers, learning rate, dropout rate, optimizer, and activation function. Outcomes refer to the test loss.;
- The aim is to identify the experiments that had the most challenging performance in terms of loss during the testing phase, along with their specific settings and results.

sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(experiment_id) AS num_experiments
FROM experiment_users
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT * 
FROM experiments 
WHERE status IN ('finished', 'error');

SELECT experiment_id
FROM hyperparameters
WHERE validate_loss_improvement_patience > 10;

SELECT *
FROM hyperparameters
WHERE experiment_id = 10;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) 
FROM experiment_users
WHERE role = 'contributor';

SELECT e.description
FROM experiments e
JOIN performance_metrics pm ON e.experiment_id = pm.experiment_id
WHERE pm.validate_loss = (
    SELECT MAX(validate_loss) FROM performance_metrics
);
